    <thetext>8.4 The String Type includes the statement &quot;each element in the String is treated as a Unicode code unit value&quot;. There is no &quot;Unicode code unit&quot;. Unicode defines three different encoding forms, UTF-8, UTF-16, and UTF-32, and each one uses different code units, namely of 8, 16, or 32 bits.

This should refer to UTF-16 code units.</thetext>
